<br>
I think the point of 61 air pet is that against higher level mobs it will hit more often and for a higher average hit and its procs will hit more often Vs epic.  If you don't have epic it is your pet of choice for grouping probably because it can not only do substantial damage but it can off tank an exp mob for a short period of time before dying.  Also encourage your friendly druid or cleric to buff your pet.  He will last much longer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ithryn>Ithryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#333333>(10/31/02 5:08:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=792.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hrrmmm...</span><hr size=1> How well does the 61+ air pet hold aggro?<br>
